   "source": [
    "# Ratings for top captions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "plt.style.use('ggplot')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import caption_contest_data as ccd"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def get_score_plot(contest, N=100):\n",
    "    df = ccd.summary(contest)   \n",
    "    scores = df.score\n",
    "    fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "    df.plot(x='rank', y='score', yerr='precision', style='_', ax=ax)\n",
    "    ax.set_xlim(0, N)\n",
    "    ax.set_ylim(scores[N], scores[0] + 0.05)\n",
    "    ax.set_title(f'Cartoon caption contest {contest}')\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel('Average score')\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('Rank')\n",
    "    return fig"
   ]
  },

   "metadata": {},
